item.name: üìÅ Planetary Positions
item.description:
All available examples for Planetary Positions endpoint. üìä **Planetary Positions Calculator** - Get precise celestial body positions

**Perfect for:**
- üéØ Quick planetary position lookups
- üì± Mobile app backends requiring fast data
- üîÑ Real-time astrological applications
- üìä Data analysis and research

**What you get:**
- **Precise positions** for all requested celestial bodies
- **Zodiac signs** (3-letter codes: Ari, Tau, Gem, etc.)
- **Degrees within signs** (0.0 to 29.99)
- **Absolute longitude** (0-360¬∞ full zodiac position)
- **Retrograde status** for all planets
- **Planetary speed** (degrees per day)

**Supported celestial bodies:**
- **Planets**: Sun, Moon, Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto
- **Lunar Nodes**: Mean_Node, True_Node, Mean_South_Node, True_South_Node
- **Angles**: Ascendant, Medium_Coeli, Descendant, Imum_Coeli
- **Points**: Mean_Lilith, True_Lilith, Pars_Fortunae, Vertex
- **Asteroids**: Chiron, Ceres, Pallas, Juno, Vesta

**Location handling:**
- Provide city + country_code for automatic geocoding
- Or use exact latitude/longitude coordinates
- Timezone automatically detected or specify manually

**Response time:** ~100ms | **Accuracy:** Swiss Ephemeris precision
- ‚úÖ **City geocoding** - just provide city name, we handle coordinates & timezone

Perfect for applications needing precise astronomical data without interpretations.

item.name: üìÅ House Cusps
item.description:
All available examples for House Cusps endpoint. üè† **House Cusps Calculator** - Precise astrological house boundaries

**Perfect for:**
- üéØ House system comparisons and analysis
- üì± Chart calculation backends
- üîÑ Real-time house position tracking
- üìä Astrological research and education

**What you get:**
- **All 12 house cusps** with precise degree positions
- **Zodiac signs** for each house cusp (3-letter codes: Ari, Tau, Gem, etc.)
- **Degrees within signs** (0.0 to 29.99)
- **Absolute longitude** (0-360¬∞ full zodiac position)
- **House system flexibility** - 23+ systems supported

**Supported house systems:**
- **P** (Placidus) - Most popular modern system
- **W** (Whole Sign) - Traditional/Hellenistic system
- **K** (Koch), **E** (Equal), **C** (Campanus)
- Plus 18 additional systems - see `/api/v3/glossary/house-systems`

**Location handling:**
- Provide city + country_code for automatic geocoding
- Or use exact latitude/longitude coordinates
- Timezone automatically detected or specify manually

**Note:** House cusps are location-dependent and require precise birth coordinates.
This endpoint provides the foundation for accurate house-based interpretations.

**Response time:** ~120ms | **Accuracy:** Swiss Ephemeris precision

item.name: üìÅ Aspects
item.description:
All available examples for Aspects endpoint. üîó **Planetary Aspects Calculator** - Precise angular relationships between celestial bodies

**Perfect for:**
- üéØ Chart interpretation and analysis
- üì± Astrology app aspect displays
- üîÑ Real-time aspect tracking
- üìä Astrological research and education

**What you get:**
- **Major aspects** between all selected celestial bodies
- **Precise orb measurements** (exact angular distance from perfect aspect)
- **Aspect types** (conjunction, opposition, trine, square, sextile, etc.)
- **Applying/separating status** for dynamic interpretation
- **Configurable precision** for orb values (0-6 decimal places)

**Supported aspects:**
- **Conjunction** (0¬∞) - Unity and blending of energies
- **Opposition** (180¬∞) - Tension and awareness
- **Trine** (120¬∞) - Harmony and flow
- **Square** (90¬∞) - Challenge and action
- **Sextile** (60¬∞) - Opportunity and cooperation
- **Plus minor aspects** - quincunx, semi-square, sesquiquadrate

**Celestial bodies included:**
- **All planets** including South Nodes (Mean_South_Node, True_South_Node)
- **Lunar Nodes** and special points
- **Flexible point selection** - choose which bodies to include

**Response time:** ~150ms | **Accuracy:** Swiss Ephemeris precision

item.name: üìÅ Lunar Metrics
item.description:
All available examples for Lunar Metrics endpoint. üåô **Comprehensive Lunar Analysis** - Detailed Moon phase and cycle information

**Perfect for:**
- üåô Lunar timing and planning
- üì± Moon phase apps and calendars
- üéØ Electional astrology (choosing optimal timing)
- üìä Agricultural and natural cycle tracking

**What you get:**
- **Current Moon phase** (New, Waxing Crescent, First Quarter, etc.)
- **Phase percentage** (0-100% illumination)
- **Days since New Moon** (lunar day count)
- **Next phase dates** (upcoming New Moon, Full Moon, etc.)
- **Lunar mansion/nakshatra** (traditional lunar divisions)
- **Void of Course periods** (when Moon makes no major aspects)

**Lunar cycle information:**
- **Synodic month** progress (29.5 day cycle)
- **Sidereal month** progress (27.3 day cycle)
- **Anomalistic month** (perigee to perigee)
- **Tropical month** (return to same zodiac degree)

**Response time:** ~150ms | **Accuracy:** Swiss Ephemeris precision

item.name: üìÅ Composite Chart
item.description:
All available examples for Composite Chart endpoint. üåü **Composite Chart Calculator** - Creates a unified chart representing the relationship itself

**Perfect for:**
- üíë **Relationship analysis** - Understanding the dynamics of partnerships
- üéØ **Couples counseling** - Professional relationship guidance
- üìö **Astrological education** - Learning composite chart techniques
- üì± **Dating apps** - Compatibility analysis features

**What you get:**
- **Composite planetary positions** - Midpoint calculations between both charts
- **Composite house cusps** - Relationship-focused house system
- **Composite aspects** - Internal aspects within the composite chart
- **Unified chart data** - Single chart representing the relationship energy

**How it works:**
The composite chart is calculated by finding the mathematical midpoints between corresponding 
planets in both natal charts. This creates a "third chart" that represents the relationship 
itself as a separate entity, showing the combined energies and themes of the partnership.

**Available options:**
- **House systems** - Placidus (P), Whole Sign (W), Koch (K), Equal (A), and more
- **Zodiac types** - Tropical (Western) or Sidereal (Vedic)
- **Active points** - Choose which planets and points to include
- **Precision** - Decimal places for degree calculations (1-6)

**Response time:** ~400ms | **Content:** Complete composite chart with planetary positions and aspects

item.description:

**Perfect for:**
- üéØ Daily astrological guidance and timing

- **Aspect direction analysis** - applying (forming), separating (dissolving), or exact
- **Precise timing calculations** - exact moment when aspects become perfect (0¬∞ orb)
- **Transit speed data** - planetary velocity for dynamic interpretation
- **Orb measurements** - exact angular distance from perfect aspects

**Analysis includes:**
- **Major life transits** (Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto)
- **Personal daily transits** (Sun, Moon, Mercury, Venus, Mars)
- **Nodal transits** for karmic timing and life direction
- **Angular transits** to Ascendant, Midheaven for major life themes

- **Aspect direction**: "applying" (forming), "separating" (dissolving), or "exact"
- **Exact timing**: ISO datetime when aspect perfects (for close applying aspects)
- **Transit speed**: Planet speed in degrees/day (negative = retrograde)

**Example response data:**

```json
{
    "date": "2024-01-15",
    "exact_time": "2024-01-15T14:32:00",
    "transiting_planet": "Mars",
    "aspect_type": "trine",
    "stationed_planet": "Sun",
    "orb": 0.75,
    "aspect_direction": "applying",
    "transiting_speed": 0.524
}
```

**Response time:** ~300ms | **Accuracy:** Swiss Ephemeris precision

item.name: üìÅ Render Natal Chart
item.description:
All available examples for Render Natal Chart endpoint. üé® **Render Natal Chart** - Generate visual birth chart in multiple formats

**Output Formats:**
- `svg` - Scalable vector (default) - best for web, infinite scaling
- `png` - Raster with transparency - universal compatibility
- `jpg` - Compressed raster - email-compatible (works in Outlook!)
- `webp` - Modern format - 30% smaller than PNG
- `pdf` - Print-ready vector - professional quality

**Size Options:**
- `width` - Output width in pixels (100-4096), height auto-calculated
- `scale` - Resolution multiplier (0.5-4.0) for HiDPI/retina displays

**Quality:**
- `quality` - For jpg/webp formats (1-100), default 90

**üé® Custom Colors (NEW!):**
Create branded charts with your own color scheme:
- `background` - Chart background color
- `text` - Text and lines color
- `primary` / `secondary` - Accent colors
- `aspect_harmony` - Harmonious aspects (green)
- `aspect_tension` - Tense aspects (red)
- `zodiac_bg_0` / `zodiac_bg_1` - Alternating zodiac sector colors

**Use Cases:**
- üìß Email reports ‚Üí `jpg` or `png` (Outlook compatible)
- üåê Web display ‚Üí `svg` or `webp`
- üì± Social media ‚Üí `jpg` with width=1080
- üñ®Ô∏è Print ‚Üí `pdf` with scale=2.0
- üì± Retina ‚Üí `png` with scale=2.0
- üé® White-label ‚Üí `custom_colors` for brand consistency

**Response time:** ~400-600ms depending on format

item.name: üìÅ Get Annual Profection
item.description:
All available examples for Get Annual Profection endpoint. üèõÔ∏è **Calculate Annual Profection (Lord of the Year)**

Returns the activated house, sign, and planetary ruler for any given age using traditional
Hellenistic methods. Essential for traditional timing techniques.

**Traditional Method:**
- Each year of life activates a different house (age mod 12)
- The ruler of the activated sign becomes the "Lord of the Year" (Chronocrator)
- Provides insights into the year's main themes and planetary influences

**Example:** At age 25, the 2nd house is activated (25 mod 12 = 1, +1 = 2nd house).
If Ascendant is Aries, the activated sign is Taurus, ruled by Venus.

**Use Cases:**
- Annual planning and timing
- Understanding yearly themes
- Traditional predictive astrology
- Life cycle analysis

item.name: üìÅ Get Traditional Analysis
item.description:
All available examples for Get Traditional Analysis endpoint. üèõÔ∏è **Comprehensive Traditional Astrology Analysis**

Generates complete traditional astrology analysis using Hellenistic techniques including:

**Perfect for:**
- üéØ Professional traditional astrology consultations
- üìö Hellenistic astrology research and study
- üîÆ Traditional timing and electional astrology
- üìä Complete dignity and reception analysis

**Dignity Analysis:**
- **Essential dignities** - domicile, exaltation, triplicity, term, decan
- **Essential debilities** - exile and fall
- **Sect analysis** - day/night chart preferences and planetary conditions

**Reception Analysis:**
- **Mutual receptions** - traditional planetary relationships
- **Dispositor chains** - complete rulership sequences and final dispositors
- **Reception quality** - dignity-based aspect interpretation

**Traditional Points:**
- **Part of Fortune** - calculated with proper day/night formulas
- **Part of Spirit** - complementary to Part of Fortune
- **Additional Arabic Parts/Lots** - traditional calculation methods

**Special Conditions:**
- **Combustion** - planets too close to the Sun (within 8.5¬∞)
- **Cazimi** - planets in the heart of the Sun (within 17 minutes)
- **Under the beams** - planets weakened by solar proximity
- **Houses of joy** - planetary jubilation in traditional houses
- **About to change sign** - planets near sign boundaries

**Input Parameters:**
- **subject** - Birth data including name and DateTimeLocation
- **options** - Chart calculation options (house system, active points, etc.)
- **orbs** - Aspect orb settings for traditional conditions

**Response time:** ~400ms | **Accuracy:** Swiss Ephemeris + Traditional calculations

item.name: üìÅ Calculate Davison Chart
item.description:
All available examples for Calculate Davison Chart endpoint. üåå **Davison Relationship Chart** - The midpoint chart of your relationship

**What is it?**
The Davison chart calculates the exact midpoint in time and space between
two births, creating a chart for the relationship itself as a separate entity.

**Calculation:**
- Midpoint in space (latitude/longitude average)
- Midpoint in time (between two birth moments)
- Creates a third chart representing the relationship

**Use cases:**
- Understanding the relationship's purpose
- Timing for the relationship
- Relationship's personality

**Response time:** ~400ms

item.name: üìÅ Generate Astrocartography Map
item.description:
All available examples for Generate Astrocartography Map endpoint. üó∫Ô∏è **Generate Astrocartography SVG Map** - Planetary influence lines on world map

**Perfect for:**
- üåç Relocation astrology consultations
- üì± Travel planning applications
- üéØ Finding power locations worldwide
- üìä Geographic astrology analysis

**What you get:**
- **Planetary lines** - AC, MC, DS, IC lines for selected planets
- **World map** - Accurate geographic projection with country boundaries
- **Power zones** - Highlighted intersections of planetary lines
- **City markers** - Major cities with population filtering
- **Interactive data** - Coordinates and meanings for frontend integration
- **Customizable** - Size, colors, projection, and styling options

**Line Types:**
- **AC (Ascendant)** - Where planet rises on eastern horizon
- **MC (Midheaven)** - Where planet culminates overhead
- **DS (Descendant)** - Where planet sets on western horizon
- **IC (Imum Coeli)** - Where planet is at lowest point

**Supported Planets:**
Sun, Moon, Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto,
Mean_Node, True_Node, Chiron

**Map Projections:**
- **Mercator** - Standard web mapping (default)
- **Robinson** - Balanced world view
- **Mollweide** - Equal-area projection
- **Equirectangular** - Simple latitude/longitude grid

**Response time:** ~800ms | **Format:** Scalable SVG with embedded data

item.name: üìÅ Render Astrocartography Map
item.description:
All available examples for Render Astrocartography Map endpoint. üó∫Ô∏è **Render Astrocartography Map** - Multi-format map generation

**Output Formats:**
- `svg` - Scalable vector (default) - best for web, interactive features
- `png` - Raster with transparency - email reports (Outlook compatible!)
- `jpg` - Compressed raster - social media sharing
- `webp` - Modern format - 30% smaller than PNG
- `pdf` - Print-ready vector - professional consultations

**Size Options:**
- `width` - Output width in pixels (100-4096)
- `scale` - Resolution multiplier for HiDPI displays

**üé® Custom Colors:**
Override default theme colors for branded maps:
- `background`, `text`, `primary`, `secondary`
- `aspect_harmony`, `aspect_tension`

**Use Cases:**
- üìß Email reports ‚Üí `png` or `jpg` (Outlook compatible)
- üåê Web display ‚Üí `svg` (interactive, scalable)
- üì± Social media ‚Üí `jpg` with width=1200
- üñ®Ô∏è Print ‚Üí `pdf` with scale=2.0
- üé® White-label ‚Üí `custom_colors` for brand consistency

**Response time:** ~800-1200ms depending on format and complexity

- ‚úÖ **No parsing needed** - just show the text

- ‚úÖ **Emoji support** - optional visual enhancement
- ‚úÖ **Multi-language** - 11 languages supported
- ‚úÖ **Real calculations** - Swiss Ephemeris accuracy

**Format options:**
- **paragraph** (default): Connected prose text with top 3 life areas
- **bullets**: Organized list with all life areas, lucky elements, advice

- Set `use_emoji: true` for visual icons (‚≠ê, üå§Ô∏è, ‚ö†Ô∏è, üíñ, üíº, etc.)

- Perfect for modern apps and social media

**Week calculation:**
- Defaults to current week (Monday to Sunday)
- Or specify `date` for a specific week
- Always starts on Monday, ends on Sunday

**Response time:** ~200-400ms | **Zero client-side processing required**

item.name: üìÅ Generate Synastry Report
item.description:
All available examples for Generate Synastry Report endpoint. üíï **Synastry Report** - Tarot-based relationship compatibility analysis for two people

**Perfect for:**
- üíë Understanding relationship dynamics and compatibility
- üîç Exploring strengths and challenges in partnerships
- üíñ Gaining insights into romantic potential
- ü§ù Analyzing any type of relationship (romantic, business, friendship)

**How it works:**
- Draws 2 cards for each of 5 key relationship areas (10 cards total)
- Analyzes elemental harmony between cards
- Calculates weighted compatibility scores
- Optional birth card compatibility analysis

**Key relationship areas analyzed:**
- **Love** (Weight: 2.0) - Romantic attraction and emotional connection
- **Communication** (Weight: 1.8) - How you express and understand each other
- **Finance** (Weight: 1.2) - Material compatibility and shared resources
- **Spirituality** (Weight: 1.5) - Shared values and life philosophy
- **Home** (Weight: 1.4) - Domestic harmony and shared living

**Scoring system:**
- **80-95%**: Highly positive cards (2 of Cups, The Lovers, etc.)
- **50-70%**: Neutral cards with growth potential
- **20-40%**: Reversed or challenging cards
- **Bonus**: Elemental harmony between paired cards (+10%)

**Birth card compatibility (optional):**
- Calculates birth cards from birth dates
- Analyzes archetypal compatibility
- Provides deeper personality insights

**Response includes:**
- Overall compatibility score (0-100)
- Detailed analysis for each life area
- Relationship strengths and challenges
- Synthesis of overall dynamics
- All drawn cards with interpretations

**Response time:** ~250ms | **Accuracy:** Professional relationship insights

item.name: üìÅ Calculate Elemental Dignities
item.description:
All available examples for Calculate Elemental Dignities endpoint. üî• **Elemental Dignities Analysis** - Golden Dawn method for analyzing card interactions

**Perfect for:**

- ‚öñÔ∏è Identifying strengths and weaknesses in spreads
- üåü Advanced tarot interpretation techniques
- üìö Learning traditional Golden Dawn methods

**How it works:**
- **Same Element**: Cards greatly strengthen each other (2.0x)
- **Friendly Elements**: Fire+Air, Water+Earth support each other (1.5x)
- **Neutral Elements**: Fire+Earth, Air+Water balance (1.0x)
- **Opposing Elements**: Fire+Water, Air+Earth weaken each other (0.5x)

**For 3-card groups:**
- Center card is modified by flanking cards
- Average of left and right influences
- Provides combined strength and quality

**Analysis includes:**
- Individual dignity calculations for each card
- Overall elemental balance across the spread
- Strongest and weakest positions
- Dominant elemental influence
- Practical interpretation guidance

**Elemental correspondences:**
- **Fire** (Wands): Action, passion, creativity, spiritual energy
- **Water** (Cups): Emotions, intuition, relationships, healing
- **Air** (Swords): Thought, communication, conflict, clarity
- **Earth** (Pentacles): Material matters, health, practical concerns

**Response time:** ~150ms | **Method:** Traditional Golden Dawn system

All available examples for Generate Houses Spread endpoint. üè† **Astrological Houses Spread** - Complete 12-card life analysis using astrological houses

- **House 1** (Identity): Self, appearance, first impressions
- **House 2** (Finance): Money, possessions, values, resources  
- **House 3** (Communication): Siblings, short trips, daily communication
- **House 4** (Home): Family, roots, emotional foundation
- **House 5** (Creativity): Romance, children, creative expression, fun
- **House 6** (Health): Work, health, daily routines, service
- **House 7** (Relationships): Marriage, partnerships, open enemies
- **House 8** (Transformation): Shared resources, death, rebirth, occult
- **House 9** (Spirituality): Higher education, philosophy, long journeys
- **House 10** (Career): Career, reputation, social status, authority
- **House 11** (Community): Friends, hopes, dreams, group associations
- **House 12** (Spirituality/Subconscious): Hidden enemies, sacrifice, subconscious

**Angular house emphasis:**
- Houses 1, 4, 7, 10 are angular houses with 1.5x interpretive weight
- These represent the most dynamic and important life areas
- Angular cards receive deeper analysis and stronger significance

**Life area mapping:**
- Each house corresponds to specific life areas from our system
- Primary focus areas get emphasized in the interpretation
- Secondary influences are noted for comprehensive analysis

**Advanced features:**
- **Timing predictions**: House-based timing for each life area
- **Elemental dignities**: Card interactions and energy flow
- **Astrological context**: Integration with personal birth chart
- **Seasonal influences**: Natural cycles affecting each house

**Response includes:**
- 12 positioned cards with house themes
- Individual card interpretations with house context
- Life area analysis with primary/secondary emphasis
- Timing predictions for each house (optional)
- Elemental dignity calculations (optional)
- Overall synthesis and guidance

**Response time:** ~400ms | **Depth:** Professional astrological analysis
